JOS – Evangelical Church Winning All (ECWA) has condemned the attacks on the Kaduna-Abuja train, that led to the abduction of many passengers on board and the death of some persons. President of ECWA, Reverend Stephen Baba-Panyam, made the condemnation in a communique issued at the end of its 69th General Church Council (GCC) on Friday in Jos. The ECWA President also called on the Federal Government to end the constant killings and abduction of citizens of Nigeria in Kaduna, Kebbi, Zamfara, Plateau, Niger and other parts of the country facing a myriad of security challenges. ”The council condemn in strong terms the recent attack on Abuja-Kaduna bound train, the killings and abduction of passengers by terrorists as well as the invasion of the Kaduna Airport. ”Council also condemn the constant killing and abduction of citizens in Kaduna, Zamfara, Kebbi, Niger, Plateau, and other parts of the country. ”It, therefore, call on all tiers of goverment to do all it must to secure the release of all abducted victims and bring to a halt to activities of these terrorists in our nation,” he called. Baba-Panya also called on the federal government to ensure the return of the Internally Displaced Persons scattered all over the country to their original places of abodes. He advised the government to ensure the release of Nigerians who have been captured and still in the custody of their abductors. POLL The ECWA President further urged the government to support farmers with farming inputs and provide adequate security in order to improve yields and avert a looming food crisis in the country. Baba-Panya also advised the government to ensure captured terrorists were made to face the full wrath of the law, adding that such moves would serve as a deterrent to those intending to join criminal groups across the country.